<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>catch someone cold • have someone cold</xh5><p> <i>catch someone cold—</i>(<i>Sport)</i> surprise one’s opponents when they are not prepared for an attack: Northern, seeking their eighth successive League win, were <u>caught cold</u> by Castleford. </p><p><i>have someone cold</i>—(U.S. sl.) have a person in one’s power or at one’s mercy: He’ll have to take whatever deal they offer him, they’ve <u>got him cold</u> for the murder of Sedley.</p> </entry>
